About Us
About Us
Voted Best Farmer’s Market in Northeast Florida! With over 100 vendors selling fresh, local produce and homemade crafts, live music and great food, it’s sure to be fun for the entire family!
When is the market held?
Our season runs September through June, and the market is held on the 1st and 3rd Sunday of each month, except for October and March due to other Town events. Occasional variations may occur due to holidays. The Market hours are from 10am-3pm. Click here to view the
schedule
. Be sure to follow us on Facebook!
@OrangeParkMarket
Where is the market located?
The market is located at Town Hall Park on the corner of US17 and Kingsley Ave. The physical address is 2042 Park Ave, Orange Park, FL 32073. This is an outdoor, rain or shine market. Just look for the large yellow signs!
What can I expect to find at the market?
We offer a variety of quality handmade and homegrown items. You will find nearly anything your heart desires from locally grown produce, local honey, cupcakes, pies, plants, meats, raw milk, eggs, hand crafted jewelry, bird houses, pottery pieces, soaps, and much, much more.
Where do I park?
Parking is available at Town Hall and behind the Gates of Park Avenue Shopping Center.
How do I become a vendor?
All vendors are required to fill out an application. Applications can be found under the “new vendor information” tab or you can pick up an application at Town Hall or our booth at the market.
What methods of payment are accepted?
Many of our vendors accept credit cards. We do have an ATM on site at each market. As of February 4, 2018, the Market will accept SNAP/EBT cards which can be used to buy tokens which are then used to buy eligible food items. Click here for more information on the
SNAP Program
.
